node.text: Today's #GoogleDoodle encourages you to look up at the stars. Head to our homepage to see photos from @NASA's James Webb Space Telescope, including the deepest infrared photo of the universe ever taken 🤯 These awe-inspiring images will help astronomers study every phase of cosmic history, which spans a massive 13.5 billion years, and the mysteries beyond our galaxy.

node.text:
“Pictures tell us about the world, so it’s important that they do that with a sense of accuracy and beauty that maps back to our real experiences.” — Florian Koenigsberger 

Florian leads our Image Equity Initiative, helping to make sure Pixel cameras capture everyone as they truly are. Learn more about our efforts to build a world where everyone belongs at the link in bio.

node.text: This #TeacherAppreciationWeek and every week we're thankful for all the educators helping future generations grow. You can thank an educator for their encouragement, inspiration and support by sending one of the ready-to-share thank you cards from today’s Instagram Story. Tap the link in bio to hear @CCSSO National Teacher Of The Year’s Kurt Russell share his story, the importance of the teaching community and ways we're showing.

node.text: "After it became clear that Live Transcribe helps me to communicate, it became clear that we could extend it to help others,” Googler Dimitri Kanevsky says about his work as a speech research scientist. He’s developing technology like Live Transcribe to help people fully participate in the conversations around them. Learn more about our efforts to build a world where everyone belongs at the link in bio.

node.text:
Today's Teacher Appreciation Day #GoogleDoodle sends a thank-you to teachers, times infinity.

Comment below to say thank you to your favorite teacher ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Today’s Google Doodle celebrating Teacher Appreciation Week: a collage of colorful paper, stickers and flowers popping out of an envelope. A pencil forms the “L” in Google.

A real letter from a student to a teacher, written in pencil on a folded piece of white paper. It reads “Happy Teacher Appreciation Week! Dear Mrs T, I wanted to take a moment to thank YOU for being such an amazing computer science teacher. I really appreciate how approachable you are, it’s great. To know that I can talk to you about anything whether it’s class or not. Your fun and inclusive teaching style makes learning so ENJOYABLE and your guidance as a coach has taught me soooo much! Thank you for creating such a positive and supportive environment. Im truly grateful!” alongside a drawing of an apple.
A real letter from a student to a teacher. “I AM HAPPY YOU ARE MY TEACHER” is written in blue and green marker in a child’s handwriting.

A real letter from a student to a teacher, written on light pink paper with glittery heart stickers at the top. Below, written in alternating colors of marker is “You are so amazing! You could brighten anybody’s day just by one second with you! I really like how you let us play games and have extra recesses and free choices! I never wanna leave you! I also like how you are so open an understanding! You are the best teacher OF ALL TIME!”

A real letter from a student to a teacher, draw in crayon on white paper. THANK YOU is written in various colors with a heart at the center of the “o.” Below it reads “for your dedication and for inspiring me to learn and grow every day!”

A real letter from a student to a teacher, written in pencil on light yellow paper. It reads “Your a grate teacher. You alwis help me when I dont understand sumething and you alwis give alot of comfurt. I hope you keep giving all that love” with a drawing of a heart.

A real letter from a student to a teacher, written in blue ink on white paper. It reads “Thank you for being such an amazing teacher! I look forward to having your class, hearing all your ridiculous stories, and the advice you give to us that makes us better people. I appreciate you very much and I have been very lucky to be a student of yours these past two years!”

A real letter from a student to a teacher, written in pencil on lined paper. It reads, “A teacher with Talent. As I walk into school with excitement and happiness I’m greeted by an amazing teacher one full of passion and kindness. I sit at a table full of people wonder if I’ll make friends. Sitting and listening to my teacher’s lesson not wanting it to end. When the day comes to an end wishing my delightful students a wonderful weekend. My heart is full of gratitude since I teach students with an amazing, positive attitude”

This one’s for the vibe coders ✨ Today we’re releasing an updated version of Gemini 2.5 Pro with improved capabilities for coding, especially interactive web apps. Try it out by selecting Canvas and 2.5 Pro in @GoogleGemini — and tell us what you’re creating in the comments! 

Gemini 2.5 Pro Preview (I/O Edition) is also available for developers today in Google AI Studio and Vertex AI. 🧑‍💻

node.text:
Every strum of a ‘ukulele carries more than just a tune – it carries generations of vibrant culture and tradition. Today’s #GoogleDoodle honors this iconic instrument and the place it holds in Hawaiian culture as part of Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month.

Adapted from Portuguese instruments, the ‘ukulele found its true voice in Hawai‘i. Even King Kalākaua played the ‘ukulele, and it was through his embrace of hula and Hawaiian music that the ‘ukulele was able to cement its place in local music and tradition. Small, portable, and easy to learn, the ‘ukulele soon became a way to teach, share, and come together – from communities and classrooms in Hawai‘i to growing kanikapila (or jam circles) around the world. Today, it embodies Hawai‘i’s “aloha spirit.”

Ready to start your own ‘ukulele journey? It’s just a Google search away.

#Pixel9a sure is an Iris-catcher 👀

Meet the designers who made Pixel 9a feel premium in the hand and mesmerizing to the eye. With gorgeous color options, a matte back, and satin metal finishes, it’s both fun and functional.

Get a sense for it yourself at GoogleStore.com
